,"Renfrewshire, , Scotland, United Kingdom":"Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Lindsay","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Lindsey in Lincolnshire, England. This is first found in the form <i>Lindissi</i>, apparently a derivative of the British name of   Lincoln  . To this was later added the Old English element <i>ēg</i> ‘island’, since the place was virtually cut off by the surrounding fenland. The surname was taken to Scotland at an early date and is the name of an important and powerful Scottish family.","Irish: adopted as an equivalent ofvarious Gaelic names (see   Lindsey  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Linzy","meanings":["Altered form of Scottish, Irish, or English   Lindsay   or   Lindsey  . Compare   Lenzy  ."]},{"name":"Linzey","meanings":["English: variant of   Lindsay   or   Lindsey  ."]},{"name":"Lindsey","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Lindsay  .","Irish: shortened and Anglicized form of various Gaelic surnames, as for example <b>Ó Loingsigh</b> (see   Lynch   1), <b>Mac Giolla Fhionntóg</b> (see   McClintock  ), and <b>Ó Fhloinn</b> (see   Flynn   and   Lynn  )."]},{"name":"Lincoln","meanings":["English: habitational name from the city of Lincoln, so named from an original British name <i>Lindo-</i> ‘lake’ + Latin <i>colonia</i> ‘settlement, colony’. The place was an important administrative center during the Roman occupation of Britain and in the Middle Ages it was a center for the manufacture of cloth, including the famous ‘Lincoln green’.","African American: adoption of the surname in 1 above, in honor of Abraham Lincoln, the 16th president of the US, who abolished slavery.","History: Abraham Lincoln (1809–65), 16th president of the US, was the son of an illiterate laborer, descended from Samuel Lincoln, who had emigrated from England to MA in 1637."]},{"name":"Linsey","meanings":["Scottish, Irish, or English: variant of   Lindsay   or   Lindsey  .","Americanized form of German   Linse   or Swiss German <b>Linsi</b>, see   Lins  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Lindsay was born before 1384, in Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. John Lindsay. He died about 1455."},"et":{"Bef 1384–Abt 1455":"enne 1384–umbes 1455","–Female":"Surnud","1391–1452":"1391–1452","1384–1455":"1384–1455","Bef 1384":"enne 1384","1455":"1455","1452":"1452","1384":"1384","Abt 1455":"umbes 1455","1391":"1391","Renfrewshire, , Scotland, United Kingdom":"Renfrewshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Bef 1384–Abt 1455":"ennen vuotta 1384–noin 1455","–Female":"Kuollut","1391–1452":"1391–1452","1384–1455":"1384–1455","Bef 1384":"ennen vuotta 1384","1455":"1455","1452":"1452","1384":"1384","Abt 1455":"noin 1455","1391":"1391","Renfrewshire, , Scotland, United Kingdom":"Renfrewshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Bef 1384–Abt 1455":"avant 1384–environ 1455","–Female":"Décédée","1391–1452":"1391–1452","1384–1455":"1384–1455","Bef 1384":"avant 1384","1455":"1455","1452":"1452","1384":"1384","Abt 1455":"environ 1455","1391":"1391","Renfrewshire, , Scotland, United Kingdom":"Renfrewshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Scotland":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"John Lindsay est né avant 1384, à Renfrewshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs. John Lindsay. Il est décédé environ 1455."},"de":{"Bef 1384–Abt 1455":"vor 1384–um 1455","–Female":"Verstorben","1391–1452":"1391–1452","1384–1455":"1384–1455","Bef 1384":"vor 1384","1455":"1455","1452":"1452","1384":"1384","Abt 1455":"um 1455","1391":"1391","Renfrewshire, , Scotland, United Kingdom":"Renfrewshire, Schottland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scho